Howto reduce Jack XRUN when playing low latency MIDI Music

* cpu frequency governor performance:
    sudo cpufreq-set -g performance

* systemd/journald storage to RAM: 
    /etc/systemdjournald.conf: Storage=volatile

* RT kernel setup /etc/limits.d(95-audio-teaks.conf (see meta-misc/audio-tweaks)

* Avoid autostart of pulseaudio (Session/Autostart)

* Pi3: Disable Wifi (dtoverlay=pi3-disable-wifi)



Setup new music image:

REMOVE NETWORK PLUG FIRST

root:
* /etc/sddm.conf
* /etc/systemd/journald.conf
* rm /var/log/journal
* systemctl disable brcm43438.service
* systemctl disable serial-getty@ttyS0.service
* systemctl disable serial-getty@ttyAMA0.service
* in /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf: Entries (check soundcards with aplay -L)
  * defaults.ctl.card 0 -> defaults.ctl.!card "sndrpihifiberry"
  * defaults.pcm.card 0 -> defaults.pcm.!card "sndrpihifiberry"
* rm /usr/share/alsa/alsa.conf.d/*
* audioinjector: mixer control / alsactl store
* passwd

user
* passwd
* restart
* check session autostart (blueman..)
* think about reducing screen resolution
* network plug
* check journalctl output
* datetime: timezone
* jack
* qtractor...
* fluid-dssi


